        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For experienced API teams, leveraging efficient embedding models is crucial. BGE M3 python provides a robust solution for generating high-quality embeddings in production environments. This post dives into practical implementation steps."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Overview of BGE M3 for API Integration"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "BGE M3 is a state-of-the-art embedding model optimized for performance. With FP16 precision (Bge_M3_FP16), it reduces memory footprint while maintaining accuracy, making it ideal for API deployments where latency and resource usage are critical."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Setting Up BGE M3 python for Production"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "To get started with BGE M3 python, ensure your environment meets the prerequisites. Install the necessary packages using pip:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "code_block",
        "lang": "bash",
        "value": "pip install torch transformers",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "pip install torch transformers"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Load the model in Python with FP16 precision:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "code_block",
        "lang": "python",
        "value": "from transformers import AutoModel, AutoTokenizer\nimport torch\n\nmodel_name = \"BAAI/bge-m3\"\ntokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(model_name)\nmodel = AutoModel.from_pretrained(model_name, torch_dtype=torch.float16)",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "from transformers import AutoModel, AutoTokenizer"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "import torch"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": ""
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "model_name = \"BAAI/bge-m3\""
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(model_name)"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "model = AutoModel.from_pretrained(model_name, torch_dtype=torch.float16)"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Implementing Embedding Generation in APIs"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Integrate BGE M3 into your API endpoint. Here's a FastAPI example for handling embedding requests:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "code_block",
        "lang": "python",
        "value": "from fastapi import FastAPI\nimport torch\n\napp = FastAPI()\n\n@app.post(\"/embed\")\nasync def embed_text(text: str):\n    inputs = tokenizer(text, return_tensors=\"pt\", truncation=True, max_length=512)\n    with torch.no_grad():\n        outputs = model(**inputs)\n    embeddings = outputs.last_hidden_state.mean(dim=1)\n    return {\"embedding\": embeddings.squeeze().tolist()}",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "from fastapi import FastAPI"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "import torch"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": ""
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "app = FastAPI()"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": ""
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "@app.post(\"/embed\")"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "async def embed_text(text: str):"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "    inputs = tokenizer(text, return_tensors=\"pt\", truncation=True, max_length=512)"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "    with torch.no_grad():"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "        outputs = model(**inputs)"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "    embeddings = outputs.last_hidden_state.mean(dim=1)"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "code_line",
            "children": [
              {
                "text": "    return {\"embedding\": embeddings.squeeze().tolist()}"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
